entry.title: SmartCard: ensure no parallel calls on the same context
entry.content:
A PC/SC context can only handle one request at a time (exception being

SCardCancel()). Thus we have to make sure not to send a request on a

ContextId which has an ongoing call (ie, a request was sent to the

provider but its result was not yet received).



Also handling the situation where a mojom::SmartCardContext remote is

reset/destroyed but there are still mojom::SmartCardConnections created

by that context.

entry.title: Reland: Implement style containment scope tree
entry.content:
In order to be able to handle quotes (and later counters)

with respect to the "contain: style" sub trees,

a style containment scope tree has been introduced.



It manages quotes by putting them in appropriate scope, creating and

deleting scopes when necessary.



In this CL the performance regression has been fixed by not creating

the style containment scope tree until it's really needed.

entry.title: FLEDGE: Enable screen height as unit and pure numbers input for ad
entry.content:
size.



Currently, for generateBid() and joinAdInterestGroup(), the supported

ad size units are

* "px": pixel

* "sw": screen width



This CL adds the unit:

* "sh": screen height



The parser is also updated to support parsing pure numbers as pixels.

For example, "100" is parsed as 100 pixels.



A regular expression is used to match the input, and capture the

sub-patterns for value and unit.

^\s*((?:0|(?:[1-9][0-9]*))(?:\.[0-9]+)?)(px|sw|sh)?\s*$



It basically means we match

1. Zero or more leading spaces.

2. Numbers, with optionally decimal point and digits. No leading space, cannot begin with zero, non-negative. (Sub-pattern captured)

3. Immediately followed by an unit which can be one of "px", "sw" or "sh", or the unit can be ignored entirely.

entirely. (Sub-pattern captured)

4. Zero or more trailing spaces.



Bug: http://b/239866637



See Turtledove issue: https://github.com/WICG/turtledove/issues/312

entry.title: Stop sending the StyleSheet pointer through ElementRuleCollector.
entry.content:
We don't really need to associate every given MatchedRule with

which style sheet it came from; it is only needed for devtools,

and for that, we can search through all stylesheets for the rule

since it's not as performance-critical.



This is both a small cleanup, and a preparation for having RuleSets

that contain rules from multiple different stylesheets (superrulesets).



For devtools, we now need to know the style scope we are matching

against, so that we know what stylesheets to search through.

Since this information was lost before AddMatchedRulesToTracker()

was called, we're now moving the AddMatchedRulesToTracker()

call further in to get it to run a bit earlier.

entry.title: [sync] Fix metric about trusted vault error state upon first sync
entry.content:
Before this patch: in many cases but not always, by the time the

metric-recording code is exercised, IsSyncFeatureEnabled() returned

false, which prevented the recording of the metric.



With this patch, the metric-recording code is exercised also when

IsSyncFeatureEnabled() transitions from false to true. This has a

negligible effect on metrics Sync.TrustedVaultErrorShownOnStartup*,

but significantly impacts metric

Sync.TrustedVaultErrorShownOnFirstTimeSync, which is now renamed.

entry.title: Adding support for clearing CORS PreflightCache on clearing browser data
entry.content:
Makes the necessary changes to provide the CORS PreflightCache with the

ability to remove its contents when the user clears the browser data,

more specifically cached images and files.



Clear browsing history allows to clear information for the last 1hr,

24hr, 7d, 4w, and all time.



The PreflightCache does not contain a timestamp for when the entry was

added to the cache, and since Chrome caps the Access-Control-Max-Age

header value for CORS-preflight responses to 2hrs, this implementation

does not support for partial deletion based on the specified timeframe.

Instead, it clears the PreflightCache contents for "all-time" and according to the ClearDataFilter specified.

entry.title: Reland "inputs: Fix OnCursorPosition/OnCommitString in Lacros."
entry.content:
This reverts commit c91ce23a4fc50122b25d8543327dc1e44f8b2fa3.



Reason for revert: Relanding behind flag with tests.



Because the fix here is not observable without https://crrev.com/c/4394605, we can't write a test in this CL. However, the tests in https://crrev.com/c/4394605 will fail without this CL, showing that this fix is doing something.



Original change's description:

> Revert "inputs: Fix OnCursorPosition/OnCommitString in Lacros."

>

> This reverts commit 0bcbfa3bd4ead1e3ed83160552117d04dafea69a.

>

> Reason for revert: crbug.com/1412998

>

> Original change's description:

> > inputs: Fix OnCursorPosition/OnCommitString in Lacros.

> >

> > In Lacros, ConfirmCompositionText is broken down to two operations:

> > - set_cursor with current selection

> > - commit_string ""

> >

> > When calling set_cursor, we flip the selection start/end [1]. But we

> > forgot to flip it back [2] on the Lacros side.

> >

> > So set_cursor(0, 4) becomes set_cursor(4, 0) on the other end. This

> > completely breaks the ConfirmCompositionText behaviour when there's a

> > selection.
